FT  25 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Allied Radio incurs Pounds 1.7m loss
Allied Radio reported a pre-tax loss of Pounds 1.72m in the nine months to
September 30, on turnover of Pounds 4.55m.
For the comparable period - covering the 1991 year - the group incurred
losses of Pounds 1.57m before tax.
The latest figure included a charge of Pounds 454,000 to amortise the
goodwill from the acquisition of Radio Mercury and County Sound in September
1991, plus Pounds 181,000 for the rationalisation of property requirements.
The trading loss was Pounds 763,000, compared with Pounds 464,000.
Losses per share were 3.4p (23.8p for 1991).
